sentences.english: You went into far Ku-to-yen, by the river of swirling eddies.
sentences.chinese: 你去了瞿塘灩澦堆，緊挨着那條河，密密麻麻的漩渦。

sentences.english: Don't crowd the notebook. Leave space for annotating notes.
sentences.chinese: 不要記得密密麻麻，留下補記的空間。

sentences.english: Everywhere on the mountain there are thickly dotted pine and cypress trees.
sentences.chinese: 山上到處都是密密麻麻的松柏林。

sentences.english: It is replaced by new leaves dense, shade built a whole tree.
sentences.chinese: 它換新的葉子密密麻麻，蔭蓋了整棵樹。

sentences.english: Books with dense print can be difficult to read.
sentences.chinese: 印得密密麻麻的書閱讀起來很困難。

sentences.english: The main stream of subway station is more like marching ants generally crowded.
sentences.chinese: 主要地鐵站口的人流更是如螞蟻行軍一般密密麻麻的。

sentences.english: So, painstakingly, he combed the thatch of the past.
sentences.chinese: 在彌留之際，他艱難地梳理密密麻麻的往事。
